com.github.ozcanturkmen.ontocsv

Class InstancePopulator

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.ozcanturkmen.ontocsv.InstancePopulator

  • public class InstancePopulator
extends Object
    InstancePopulator class provides the methods to populate an OWL ontology (in RDF/XML format) with instances provided via CSV (comma separated values) files.

    Class and instance names are expected to be provided as separate csv files.

    The class makes use of the Apache JENA library to create an in-memory ontology model using OntModelSpec.OWL_DL_MEM specification. It creates the instances for the given classes as named individuals within the ontology.

    Created by on 19.02.2020

      • getNormalizedInstanceName

        protected static String getNormalizedInstanceName(String instanceName)
        Normalizes instance name by evaluating common punctuation marks. Spaces are replaced with underscores, the string gets trimmed and converted to lowercase letters.
        Parameters:

        Returns:

      • create

        public static Optional<InstancePopulator> create(String path,
                                                 String... otherPathParts)
        Factory method with path parameter to create an InstancePopulator instance.

        Provide the path of directory using path and otherPathParts parameters. Method inspects that directory to automatically identify the ontology file (must be an .owl file), along with two csv files, one meant for class names, and the other for instances.

        Among the csv files, the smallest in size will be assumed as the input file for class names.

        Parameters:
        path - string, path to ontology and csv input files
        otherPathParts - string, remaining parts of the path (if any) as varargs
        Returns:
        Optional of InstancePopulator
        See Also:
        Optional

      • process

        public int process()
        Creates individuals, and adds them to the ontology.

        In order to not override the original ontology file, it produces a new ontology file (generated.owl) which will contain the newly introduced instances.

        Accumulates the skipped csv lines in a skipped.txt file, and reports the number of processes instances.

        Between the instantiation of the InstancePopulator and the invocation of this process method, there should be a Optional.ifPresent(java.util.function.Consumer<? super T>) check to make sure that the instantiation was successful.

        Returns:
        int Number of created individuals
